UBS Group AG Key Developments

UBS Group AG Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Year to Date Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 28 17
UBS Group AG reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and year to date ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, on consolidated basis, the company reported total operating income of CHF 7,269 million compared to CHF 7,404 million for the same period a year ago. Operating profit before tax was CHF 1,502 million compared to CHF 1,489 million for the same period a year ago. Net profit attributable to the company shareholders was CHF 1,174 million compared to CHF 1,034 million for the same period a year ago. Diluted earnings per share was CHF 0.31 compared to CHF 0.27 for the same period a year ago. Net interest income was CHF 1,417 million compared to CHF 1,164 million for the same period a year ago. Return on equity was 8.9% compared to 7.7% for the same period a year ago. Return on tangible equity was 8.9% compared to 10.3% for the same period a year ago. Return on assets, gross was 3.4% compared to 3.3% for the same period a year ago. Adjusted net profit attributable to the company shareholders was CHF 1,174 million compared to CHF 1,034 million for the same period a year ago. 

For the year to date, the company reported operating income of CHF 14,801 million compared to CHF 14,237 million for the same period a year ago. Operating profit before tax was CHF 3,192 million compared to CHF 2,467 million for the same period a year ago. Net profit attributable to the company shareholders was CHF 2,443 million compared to CHF 1,741 million for the same period a year ago. Diluted earnings per share was CHF 0.64 compared to CHF 0.45 for the same period a year ago. Return on equity was 9.2% compared to 6.4% for the same period a year ago. Return on tangible equity was 10.6% compared to 7.4% for the same period a year ago. Return on assets, gross was 3.4% compared to 3.2% for the same period a year ago. Total book value per share was CHF 13.92 as on June 30, 2017 compared to CHF 14.27 as on June 30, 2016. Tangible total book value per share was CHF 12.25 as on June 30, 2017 compared to CHF 12.54 as on June 30, 2016. Net interest income was CHF 3,113 million compared to CHF 2,876 million for the same period a year ago. On an adjusted basis, operating profit before tax declined to CHF 3,609 million from CHF 3,038 million, reflecting a decrease in operating income, partly offset by lower operating expenses.


UBS Group AG, Q2 2017 Earnings Call, Jul 28, 2017
Jul 14 17
UBS Group AG, Q2 2017 Earnings Call, Jul 28, 2017


HSBC Holdings Plc and UBS Group AG Settle US Rate-Rigging Litigation
Jul 11 17
HSBC Holdings Plc and UBS Group AG have each agreed to pay $14 million to settle private U.S. litigation accusing them of rigging an interest rate benchmark used in the $483 trillion derivatives market. The preliminary settlements were disclosed in filings in the U.S. District Court in Manhattan and require a judge's approval. They boost the total payout from 10 settling banks to $408.5 million. HSBC and UBS denied wrongdoing. Several pension funds and municipalities had accused 14 banks of conspiring to rig the ISDAfix benchmark for their own gain from at least 2009 to 2012. Companies and investors use ISDAfix to price swaps transactions, commercial real estate mortgages and structured debt securities. The eight earlier settlements have won preliminary approval. Payouts include $56.5 million from Goldman Sachs Group Inc; $52 million from JPMorgan Chase & Co; $50 million from each of Bank of America Corp, Credit Suisse Group AG, Deutsche Bank AG and Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc; $42 million from Citigroup Inc. and $30 million from Barclays Plc, court papers showed. BNP Paribas SA, Morgan Stanley, Nomura Holdings Inc. and Wells Fargo & Co have not settled, the papers showed.


