Dorman Products, Inc. (DORM) Shares Sold by UBS Group AG

					Posted by Kim Johansen on Jul 25th, 2017 // No Comments 




UBS Group AG decreased its stake in shares of  Dorman Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:DORM) by 8.3% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 52,632 shares of the auto parts company’s stock after selling 4,786 shares during the period. UBS Group AG owned about 0.15% of Dorman Products worth $4,323,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds also recently bought and sold shares of the stock. Vanguard Group Inc. raised its position in shares of  Dorman Products by 4.8% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 2,806,822 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $230,525,000 after buying an additional 127,653 shares during the last quarter.  Congress Asset Management Co. MA raised its position in shares of  Dorman Products by 8.5% in the first quarter. Congress Asset Management Co. MA now owns 935,503 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $76,833,000 after buying an additional 73,446 shares during the last quarter.  Dimensional Fund Advisors LP raised its position in  Dorman Products by 1.0% in the fourth quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 844,321 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $61,687,000 after buying an additional 8,368 shares in the last quarter.  State Street Corp raised its position in  Dorman Products by 7.9% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 598,056 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $43,696,000 after buying an additional 43,770 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Bank of New York Mellon Corp raised its position in  Dorman Products by 32.9% in the first quarter. Bank of New York Mellon Corp now owns 542,854 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $44,585,000 after buying an additional 134,472 shares in the last quarter. 77.06% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Dorman Products Inc. alerts:



Dorman Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:DORM) traded up 0.95% during mid-day trading on Tuesday, hitting $77.53. 100,981 shares of the stock traded hands. The firm’s 50-day moving average is $79.49 and its 200-day moving average is $77.97. Dorman Products, Inc. has a 12-month low of $56.10 and a 12-month high of $88.50. The company has a market cap of $2.66 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 24.15 and a beta of 0.63. 




Dorman Products (NASDAQ:DORM) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 2nd. The auto parts company reported $0.85 EPS for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.79 by $0.06. Dorman Products had a net margin of 12.66% and a return on equity of 18.79%. The company had revenue of $221.60 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $224.16 million. During the same period in the prior year, the firm earned $0.71 earnings per share. The business’s quarterly revenue was up 6.4% on a year-over-year basis.  Equities research analysts expect that  Dorman Products, Inc. will post $3.47 EPS for the current year. 
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY WARNING: This piece of content was originally  published by Markets Daily and is owned by of Markets Daily. If you are viewing this piece of content on another publication, it was copied illegally and reposted in violation of US and international trademark & copyright legislation. The legal version of this piece of content can be viewed at https://www.themarketsdaily.com/2017/07/25/ubs-group-ag-cuts-stake-in-dorman-products-inc-dorm-updated-updated.html. 
Several equities analysts have issued reports on the stock. B. Riley  reaffirmed a “neutral” rating and issued a $74.50 price target on shares of Dorman Products in a report on Saturday, May 13th. BidaskClub raised shares of Dorman Products from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Saturday, June 24th. FBR & Co  reissued a “mkt perform” rating and set a $74.50 price objective on shares of Dorman Products in a report on Tuesday, July 18th. Zacks Investment Research downgraded shares of Dorman Products from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research report on Monday, July 10th. Finally, Jefferies Group LLC  reiterated a “hold” rating and issued a $85.00 price objective (up previously from $78.00) on shares of Dorman Products in a research report on Wednesday, May 3rd. One investment analyst  has rated the stock with a sell rating and four have issued  a hold rating to the stock. The company presently has a consensus rating of “Hold” and a consensus price target of $81.25.
In other Dorman Products news, Director Paul R. Lederer sold 7,593 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction dated Friday, May 5th. The shares were sold at an average price of $82.70, for a total transaction of $627,941.10. Following the completion of the sale, the director now directly owns 15,873 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $1,312,697.10. The transaction was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available through this link. 11.70% of the stock is currently owned by corporate insiders. 
Dorman Products Company Profile
Dorman Products, Inc is a supplier of replacement parts and fasteners for passenger cars, light trucks and heavy duty trucks in the automotive aftermarket. As of December 31, 2016, the Company distributed and marketed approximately 155,000 different stock keeping units (SKU’s) of automotive replacement parts and fasteners.







